1
00:00:04,590 --> 00:00:06,800
Once this rivalry is settled,

2
00:00:08,140 --> 00:00:08,900
what...

3
00:00:10,170 --> 00:00:11,290
will become of us?

4
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:14,880
Who knows?

5
00:00:19,210 --> 00:00:20,270
We probably...

6
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:22,950
won't even be able to stay friends.

7
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:35,520
Hey,

8
00:00:36,180 --> 00:00:36,810
Zen.

9
00:00:38,060 --> 00:00:38,850
What?

10
00:00:42,980 --> 00:00:44,780
Maybe we should just call off...

11
00:00:45,580 --> 00:00:46,450
this rivalry.

12
00:00:49,050 --> 00:00:49,530
What?

13
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:51,820
Call it off

14
00:00:51,850 --> 00:00:52,610
now?

15
00:00:55,540 --> 00:00:56,870
Just kidding!

16
00:00:57,740 --> 00:00:58,400
Huh?

17
00:00:58,540 --> 00:01:00,750
You totally fell for it.

18
00:01:00,780 --> 00:01:01,540
I did not.

19
00:01:01,930 --> 00:01:03,280
You know, right?

20
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:05,150
If you run away, you lose.

21
00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:07,020
This is a showdown, after all.

22
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:13,940
I know.

23
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:19,780
[Fake Fact Lips]

24
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:25,180
[Episode 5:
You're Really Hard to Figure Out!]

25
00:02:41,810 --> 00:02:42,420
Director?

26
00:02:42,890 --> 00:02:43,980
You've worked hard.

27
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:44,840
This is for you.

28
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,420
Eh? Thank you, Director.

29
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:50,700
This is the first time I've won this.
From that vending machine over there.

30
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:52,230
The one like a slot machine.

31
00:02:52,350 --> 00:02:54,060
You sure? It must mean a lot to you.

32
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:57,060
Shido, how many projects
are you working on right now?

33
00:02:57,790 --> 00:03:00,310
Noi Development, Lelt Resource,

34
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:04,090
and the new affiliate marketing project
I started researching two days ago.

35
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:04,620
Wow,

36
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:07,430
you're such a brilliant subordinate.

37
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:09,170
I've got high hopes for you.

38
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:09,800
Yes.

39
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,180
Mm?

40
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:13,960
But don't push yourself too hard!

41
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:15,750
Thank you, Director.

42
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:32,590
[I'm too busy this week.
Probably no time to meet.]

43
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:35,170
[Temporary truce.]

44
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:42,560
Good work today. What's wrong?

45
00:03:42,970 --> 00:03:44,460
Is Yotsuya in today?

46
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:46,210
He just left for a meeting.

47
00:03:46,370 --> 00:03:47,230
Oh, I see.

48
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:49,150
He'll probably be back this evening.

49
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:50,240
Did you need something from him?

50
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,400
I can pass along a message.

51
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,970
Ah, no, it's fine.

52
00:04:11,090 --> 00:04:15,100
[I left your T-shirt on your desk.]

53
00:04:22,810 --> 00:04:28,060
[You free next week?]

54
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:37,750
Yotsuya!

55
00:04:39,820 --> 00:04:40,430
Oh.

56
00:04:43,230 --> 00:04:45,560
-Um...
-I've got a business dinner later.

57
00:04:46,490 --> 00:04:47,420
Catch you later.

58
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:50,450
Oh.

59
00:05:13,810 --> 00:05:16,780
[I left your T-shirt on your desk.]

60
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:19,970
[You free next week?]

61
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:36,330
Yotsuya!

62
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:36,960
Director!

63
00:05:37,620 --> 00:05:38,540
Good work today.

64
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,600
Oh.

65
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:40,940
This Friday,

66
00:05:40,970 --> 00:05:42,760
there's a brainstorming session in Osaka.

67
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:43,540
Ah, I see.

68
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,610
I haven't sent you the data yet, right?

69
00:05:44,610 --> 00:05:46,040
But there's no rush.

70
00:05:46,060 --> 00:05:47,800
No, I might forget again otherwise.
I'll send it to you right now.

71
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,190
Just a moment.

72
00:05:49,210 --> 00:05:50,210
Sorry about that.

73
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:05,540
Let more people benefit from this service.

74
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:09,660
Together, we can make
your company's technology even stronger.

75
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:14,910
[Proposal Presentation]

76
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,340
Looking forward to working with you.

77
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:31,700
Let us clean it up.

78
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:33,370
Ah, thank you.

79
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,680
Wow, they signed on the spot.

80
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:37,220
That's our Mr. Shido.

81
00:06:37,670 --> 00:06:39,300
It's because we're an excellent team.

82
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,340
Don't be modest.

83
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,220
Your track record speaks for itself.

84
00:06:42,220 --> 00:06:44,280
The busy part is only just beginning.

85
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:48,030
We need to adjust the schedule
and confirm the budget by today.

86
00:06:48,940 --> 00:06:49,760
Mr. Shido!

87
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:50,670
Mr. Shido?

88
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:53,270
I'll go get some water for you!

89
00:06:53,290 --> 00:06:53,670
Oh!

90
00:06:59,770 --> 00:07:01,870
Sorry. I must've startled you.

91
00:07:01,890 --> 00:07:03,960
It's fine. Are you okay?

92
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:05,600
Yes, I'm fine.

93
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:07,330
Lately,

94
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:10,070
even from the outside, it's obvious
you've been overworking yourself.

95
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:12,460
Do I look overwhelmed?

96
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:14,710
It's not that exactly—

97
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:17,860
it's just that you haven't seemed
in very good spirits this week.

98
00:07:17,860 --> 00:07:20,460
Director Mishima
said something similar too.

99
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:22,400
That's embarrassing.

100
00:07:22,810 --> 00:07:24,140
Sorry for making you worry.

101
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:24,940
Please don't say that.

102
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:27,320
We've just been relying on you too much.

103
00:07:28,790 --> 00:07:30,230
At that gathering the other day,

104
00:07:30,230 --> 00:07:32,690
didn't Miss Kiritani
ask you the same thing?

105
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:35,930
She asked whether you were
taking time to relax.

106
00:07:37,890 --> 00:07:38,800
Relax...

107
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:45,130
I need to

108
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,500
sort out my own matters first.

109
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:50,610
Good work today!

110
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:52,120
Wow, Mr. Yotsuya, you really are

111
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:54,810
every bit the outstanding salesman people
say you are.

112
00:07:54,810 --> 00:07:55,409
Right?

113
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:58,380
You'd always be welcome
at the Osaka branch.

114
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,830
I'll check with HR.

115
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:01,520
Ah, if you mean it,

116
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:03,080
I'll hold you to that.

117
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:04,610
Alright then.

118
00:08:04,610 --> 00:08:06,600
Let's go grab a drink.
What do you feel like eating?

119
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,690
Fried skewers...

120
00:08:07,710 --> 00:08:08,980
Hey, you!

121
00:08:09,140 --> 00:08:11,670
Shouldn't we eat some carbs
before drinking?

122
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,820
No.

123
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:26,320
[I'm too busy this week.
Probably no time to meet.]

124
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,720
[Temporary truce.]

125
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:32,860
Eh? You picked up so quickly.

126
00:08:33,860 --> 00:08:34,620
What?

127
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:36,600
Nothing really.

128
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:40,539
That project I'd been busy with
finally wrapped up.

129
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:46,100
Sorry.

130
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,280
Why are you apologizing?

131
00:08:49,980 --> 00:08:51,010
Um...

132
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,930
For not replying to your messages.

133
00:08:54,580 --> 00:08:56,470
You mean you were avoiding me?

134
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,930
No, it's not that.

135
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:02,820
You don't have to check in with me
every time something like that happens.

136
00:09:02,820 --> 00:09:03,820
But...

137
00:09:04,730 --> 00:09:07,190
I was busy preparing
for a presentation too.

138
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,140
I didn't have time for you either.

139
00:09:11,060 --> 00:09:11,730
I see.

140
00:09:13,410 --> 00:09:15,390
You said you were busy, which means

141
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:17,490
things wrapped up

142
00:09:17,810 --> 00:09:19,140
on your side too, right?

143
00:09:19,820 --> 00:09:21,220
The presentation's over.

144
00:09:21,220 --> 00:09:22,680
But the real work is only starting now.

145
00:09:22,680 --> 00:09:24,270
Oh, so it went through.

146
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,560
As expected of you.

147
00:09:25,710 --> 00:09:26,680
Of course.

148
00:09:27,170 --> 00:09:28,830
Don't push yourself too hard.

149
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:31,510
You haven't crashed yet, have you?

150
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,250
As if.

151
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:36,280
So how are things on your end?

152
00:09:36,660 --> 00:09:37,430
On my end?

153
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:39,620
Nothing much has changed.

154
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:41,620
But...

155
00:09:42,770 --> 00:09:44,350
I might be a little tired.

156
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:48,170
So...

157
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:49,680
how do I put this?

158
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:53,870
I just really wanted to hear

159
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,480
your voice.

160
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:00,300
But...

161
00:10:02,530 --> 00:10:03,530
just as I thought—

162
00:10:03,860 --> 00:10:05,520
the moment I heard your voice,

163
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:07,420
I wanted to see you.

164
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,420
Yotsuya!

165
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,430
We've already booked the restaurant!

166
00:10:15,430 --> 00:10:16,520
Coming!

167
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:17,760
Ryo!

168
00:10:19,050 --> 00:10:20,380
Where are you right now?

169
00:10:20,610 --> 00:10:22,480
Right now? Osaka.

170
00:10:24,050 --> 00:10:24,740
Osaka.

171
00:10:25,230 --> 00:10:25,700
Mm.

172
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:28,880
I'm going to stay for another night.

173
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:32,010
I've got to go drink with them.

174
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,830
I'll talk to you when I get back.

175
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,240
Ah, Mr. Shido!

176
00:10:41,270 --> 00:10:42,650
Sorry, but someone just called.

177
00:10:42,650 --> 00:10:43,660
Ah, sorry.

178
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:45,210
I'm heading home for today.

179
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:46,850
There shouldn't be anything urgent.

180
00:10:46,850 --> 00:10:48,660
Please tell them
we'll handle it next week.

181
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:49,590
Got it.

182
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:52,410
That's so far away.

183
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,250
Do you have somewhere to be?

184
00:10:55,380 --> 00:10:55,950
No.

185
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:57,490
Just...

186
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,660
relaxing a bit.

187
00:11:18,490 --> 00:11:19,130
Ryo!

188
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:45,950
You said you wanted to see me.

189
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:55,630
What's with that reaction?

190
00:11:55,630 --> 00:11:56,810
Try acting a little happier.

191
00:11:56,810 --> 00:11:57,770
Great!

192
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:02,180
I'm so happy.

193
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,570
You feel so cold.

194
00:12:24,740 --> 00:12:25,760
Then,

195
00:12:26,610 --> 00:12:28,070
you know what to do, right?

196
00:12:58,520 --> 00:12:59,330
Ryo!

197
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:01,750
Mm?

198
00:13:07,330 --> 00:13:08,360
Ryo...

199
00:13:09,770 --> 00:13:13,030
You're doing all this
just because of the showdown, right?

200
00:13:17,010 --> 00:13:18,240
Isn't that...

201
00:13:21,780 --> 00:13:23,050
the same for you?

202
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:27,470
I...

203
00:13:30,950 --> 00:13:31,660
Zen.

204
00:13:35,810 --> 00:13:37,220
Why are you crying?

205
00:13:38,050 --> 00:13:39,320
I'm not!

206
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:46,230
Ryo.

207
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:50,620
As long as you can win,
you'd do this with anyone?

208
00:13:52,030 --> 00:13:52,630
Eh?

209
00:13:54,550 --> 00:13:56,240
You want to beat me that badly?

210
00:13:57,190 --> 00:13:58,020
No.

211
00:13:58,040 --> 00:13:59,630
Then what is it?

212
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:02,380
Why are we...

213
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:05,510
doing any of this?

214
00:14:23,190 --> 00:14:24,170
Actually...

215
00:14:27,990 --> 00:14:29,510
from the very beginning,

216
00:14:29,830 --> 00:14:31,890
the showdown never really mattered.

217
00:14:36,270 --> 00:14:36,840
I

218
00:14:37,590 --> 00:14:38,200
just...

219
00:14:41,570 --> 00:14:43,110
wanted to be with you.

220
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,690
I've always liked you.

221
00:14:50,230 --> 00:14:52,300
Ever since high school.

222
00:14:55,410 --> 00:14:56,000
What?

223
00:14:57,010 --> 00:14:58,010
So...

224
00:15:01,090 --> 00:15:03,940
I didn't come on to you to win.

225
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,650
I genuinely wanted you.

226
00:15:18,740 --> 00:15:21,000
Sorry for using such dishonest methods.

227
00:15:23,070 --> 00:15:25,480
I lost this showdown from the very start.

228
00:15:28,460 --> 00:15:29,150
Zen...

229
00:15:31,060 --> 00:15:32,270
In that case,

230
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:35,440
be my boyfriend.

231
00:15:37,430 --> 00:15:38,110
What?

232
00:15:40,890 --> 00:15:42,220
Since I've won you over,

233
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,760
I have to see it through
to the end, right?

234
00:15:48,090 --> 00:15:49,060
What do you mean?

235
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:51,030
Because...

236
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,010
the winner calls the shots,

237
00:15:55,110 --> 00:15:55,930
right?

238
00:16:04,090 --> 00:16:05,110
Say something.

239
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:09,480
Sorry.

240
00:16:12,310 --> 00:16:13,770
My head's a mess right now.

241
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:14,980
Why?

242
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,200
Well...

243
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:22,480
Um...

244
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:26,450
We talked about this before, right?

245
00:16:28,090 --> 00:16:30,420
About what happens when the rivalry ends.

246
00:16:31,340 --> 00:16:33,680
You mean when you said
you wanted to call it off?

247
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:35,360
That time was on me.

248
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,730
At that time, you said...

249
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:41,140
We probably...

250
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,730
won't even be able to stay friends.

251
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:46,660
Huh?

252
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:51,000
Obviously, we'd become
something more than friends.

253
00:16:55,510 --> 00:16:57,450
You're really hard to figure out!

254
00:16:57,470 --> 00:16:58,440
Huh?

255
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:01,180
Do you know

256
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:04,369
how torn I was after hearing that?

257
00:17:04,859 --> 00:17:07,119
Did you really just take it at face value?

258
00:17:07,510 --> 00:17:08,550
You're one to talk.

259
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:10,560
How could you be this dense?

260
00:17:10,579 --> 00:17:12,710
If I couldn't be with you,

261
00:17:14,849 --> 00:17:16,470
I'd rather...

262
00:17:17,930 --> 00:17:19,450
stay your friend forever.

263
00:17:23,420 --> 00:17:26,250
Then I realized I'd crossed a line
I couldn't come back from.

264
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:28,300
I genuinely regretted it.

265
00:17:31,090 --> 00:17:33,020
If I hadn't managed to win you over,

266
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:35,340
I...

267
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,830
I could've lost you forever.

268
00:17:43,990 --> 00:17:44,730
Ryo.

269
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,430
So...

270
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:52,200
if you wanted to be with me,

271
00:17:53,390 --> 00:17:55,850
you should've just admitted defeat sooner!

272
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,470
Says the one who has liked me

273
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:58,690
from the very beginning.

274
00:17:58,690 --> 00:17:59,680
You really hate losing, don't you?

275
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,800
So do you!

276
00:18:01,740 --> 00:18:02,600
For the record,

277
00:18:02,810 --> 00:18:04,220
don't get it wrong.

278
00:18:04,470 --> 00:18:06,130
It's because you tried so hard

279
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,410
that I was finally won over.

280
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:13,220
Come on.

281
00:18:13,250 --> 00:18:15,150
You're not honest at all.

282
00:18:20,490 --> 00:18:21,350
But...

283
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:26,130
that's exactly what I like about you.

284
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:28,740
You...

285
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:33,480
being this straightforward all of a sudden
is a bit much for me to handle.

286
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:34,400
Even so...

287
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:39,250
I'm done with us missing each other

288
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:43,450
just because neither of us
would say what we really feel.

289
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:44,900
You're such an idiot,

290
00:18:45,860 --> 00:18:48,190
taking some silly showdown so seriously.

291
00:18:49,260 --> 00:18:50,470
I'm the same.

292
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:55,440
Everyone turns into a fool

293
00:18:56,890 --> 00:18:58,950
when it comes to the person they love.

294
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:02,880
Zen...

295
00:19:06,940 --> 00:19:07,840
I like you.

296
00:19:12,310 --> 00:19:12,970
Me too.

297
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:16,220
I want you,

298
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:19,120
and no one else.

299
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:21,710
Sorry.

300
00:19:22,780 --> 00:19:23,580
I'm afraid...

301
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:27,060
I can't hold back anymore.

302
00:19:44,190 --> 00:19:45,450
Now you really...

303
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:49,310
can't be with anyone but me.

304
00:19:52,490 --> 00:19:53,400
No.

305
00:19:55,030 --> 00:19:56,500
I've long been like that.

306
00:19:58,530 --> 00:19:59,930
I can't live without you.

307
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:25,780
Whenever I'm with you,

308
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:27,560
I go a little crazy.

309
00:21:29,170 --> 00:21:30,180
I'll take that

310
00:21:31,490 --> 00:21:33,420
as a compliment.

311
00:21:34,140 --> 00:21:35,630
Suit yourself.

312
00:21:38,830 --> 00:21:39,590
Zen.

313
00:21:43,060 --> 00:21:44,350
Only look at me.

314
00:22:35,170 --> 00:22:36,430
Hey, Zen.

315
00:22:40,970 --> 00:22:42,570
Let's go somewhere together

316
00:22:43,170 --> 00:22:44,220
after the test.

317
00:22:44,990 --> 00:22:47,190
We've got the exams coming up, you know.

318
00:22:47,940 --> 00:22:50,120
If I go out every time an exam ends,

319
00:22:51,450 --> 00:22:53,310
I'll never catch up to my brother.

320
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:57,320
I really wish I could grow up faster.

321
00:22:58,860 --> 00:23:01,060
Why are you suddenly talking like a kid?

322
00:23:01,260 --> 00:23:02,300
Because then

323
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:04,960
I could go somewhere far away...

324
00:23:06,900 --> 00:23:08,500
and be with the person I love.

325
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:19,360
I'll take a break too.

326
00:24:27,050 --> 00:24:29,190
You told Mr. Yotsuya

327
00:24:29,220 --> 00:24:31,190
to come to our office anytime,

328
00:24:31,210 --> 00:24:32,480
you know.

329
00:24:32,970 --> 00:24:35,050
That was just a pleasantry.

330
00:24:36,330 --> 00:24:39,930
Then, Mr. Futami, are you really going
without saying anything?

331
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:42,090
A rival always comes

332
00:24:42,120 --> 00:24:44,360
when you least expect it.

333
00:24:46,130 --> 00:24:48,280
As the ace of the Osaka branch,

334
00:24:48,860 --> 00:24:51,590
I'll make a strong impression.

335
00:25:54,560 --> 00:25:57,760
[In the Next Episode]

336
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:57,150
What else do you want me to do?

337
00:25:57,170 --> 00:25:58,520
A date?

338
00:25:57,800 --> 00:26:00,850
[Episode 6: For Now, That's Unnecessary]

339
00:25:58,540 --> 00:25:59,840
Mr. Yotsuya?

340
00:25:59,870 --> 00:26:01,060
Stop joking.

341
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:01,820
Hey!

342
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:03,540
Ah.

343
00:26:03,670 --> 00:26:04,610
Really?

344
00:26:04,630 --> 00:26:07,450
I've liked you since college.

345
00:26:07,470 --> 00:26:09,860
You just took back first place,

346
00:26:09,890 --> 00:26:11,860
and you're already getting so cocky, huh?

347
00:26:11,860 --> 00:26:12,760
Yes, I won't!

348
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:14,150
Ah!

349
00:26:14,170 --> 00:26:14,930
Huh?

350
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:18,160
Don't be fooled—
they actually respect each other.

351
00:26:18,190 --> 00:26:20,150
You should be careful too, Mr. Shido.

352
00:26:20,150 --> 00:26:22,440
Time together is precious.
